# Voyager Sanctuary — Firebase Android deploy

## Always send a build when ready for testing

Whenever the app is **ready for user testing** (e.g. after a chunk of work that makes it testable, gatekeepers done, or a release candidate), **run the deploy script** so testers get the build. Do **not** wait for the user to prompt. From repo root `voyager_sanctuary`:

- **Windows (PowerShell):** `.\deploy.ps1 -ReleaseNotes "Short notes"`

If the script fails (e.g. `firebase` not logged in or not in PATH), report the error and remind the user of one-time setup (`firebase login`); still record in the session that a build was due.

After finishing a **major UI or onboarding change** (e.g. stagger timing, Return/Continue, new screens, RLS or save flows), treat the app as ready for testing and trigger a build as above.

## Auto deploy (in addition to manual)

- **Cursor:** `.cursor/hooks.json` runs `.cursor/hooks/auto-firebase-deploy.ps1` on agent **`stop`** when `lib/`, `pubspec.yaml`, or `android/` have uncommitted changes (deduped by fingerprint). Requires opening the **`voyager_sanctuary` folder** as the Cursor workspace so project hooks load; restart Cursor after hook changes.
- **GitHub:** `.github/workflows/firebase-app-distribution.yml` uploads on push to `main`/`master` when Flutter paths change, if secret **`FIREBASE_TOKEN`** is set (`firebase login:ci`).

## Deploy script (canonical)

- **`deploy.ps1`** (repo root): bumps `pubspec` `+build`, `flutter build apk --release`, `firebase appdistribution:distribute` to group `testers`.

## One-time setup (user runs in terminal)

1. `firebase login` — CLI auth for the project (local builds)
2. For CI: `firebase login:ci` → add token as GitHub secret `FIREBASE_TOKEN`
